I am available for adoption; however due to my breed my adoption will have to be facilitated through a rescue organization. Please see the front desk staff or contact the Shelter at (248) 858-1070 for more information.

Meet Daisy! Beautiful Daisy, has had a rough start to 2021. She spent the last 3 months in a home, where she was very cared for. Daisy was so excited to be in her new home, that she would get wiggly and jumpy. She is house trained, does amazing with children, does well with other dogs, and is an exuberant girl. Daisy is deserving of a home where she can learn lots of new things, be included in all the goings on and be loved for her lifetime!

The following descriptions describe behaviors that were observed during testing and/or veterinary examination: Evaluated for temperament with 336985 (male), and 336940 (female). Did well with both. She was very wiggly with male. She is a previous quarantine dog, bit owner when he was letting her outside. She is very high energy, jumps on people, and can be nippy when overstimulated. Suspect that is what prompted "bite" 1/27/2021

American Pit Bulls are a misunderstood breed; for this reason, we implore adopters to these beautiful dogs to be very vigilant in training and socialization. This breed is very energetic and will need daily exercise. Because of their strength and energy, apartment living may not be the best fit. This breed can be loving, loyal and very smart. 

The above behaviors and personality traits have been observed while at the Shelter. If this animal was relinquished, information is gathered from the owner regarding behavior. Our wonderful volunteers spend time with these animals and give input on behaviors and traits. However, this description may not be all inclusive to how this animal will act in a loving forever home. Introduction to established family pets should be slow and monitored always. The same goes for children and other family members. Adopting a pet is a big decision and should be thoughtful. We suggest researching different breeds to match traits and personalities to your lifestyle. When adopting a pet, please know that this pet will be with you for their lifetime; patience and consistency will make for a successful adoption.

This dog has bitten or scratched in the past. The Shelter staff feel as though it was an accident; the dog was playing and it just got a little out of hand and a bite or scratch happened. In this case the Shelter strongly recommends training and socializing this dog so that an accident will be prevented in the future. Teaching the dog not to jump when excited or playing will go a long way in preventing this from happening again.

animal.description:
COURTSEY LISTING
Hi friends, my name is Cinnamon. I am a 6 year old Red nose Pitbull (female). I am a huge love bug who enjoys being around adults and kids! I have grown up around children my whole life, and love to snuggle with anyone who will give me love. I am a huge couch potato and have to be around someone to feel safe and loved. I act like a puppy sometimes, full of excitement and love adventures. I enjoy hiking, car rides, sun bathing in the sun, and chew toys! I am highly motivated by food and know a few commands. I try my best not to jump up on to people, but I can't always contain myself. I am a HUGE licker and snuggle bug. 

I've lived with the same family my whole life. I love them and they love me but my family has to move to a place that won't allow me to come along. My mom is hoping to find someone that might let me crash with them for a little while (maybe 12-14 months) while she looks for a new home where we can all be together again. I have a 5 year old human sister who I have grown up with and mom just had another baby sister who is less than a month old. My mom is a Marine Veteran so she is dedicated to me and getting me back home with her the future. Mom is hoping to find someone that will help take care of me until we can all be together again someday and our new friends at K9 Kismet have agreed to help.  If you'd like to meet up please reach out to the folks at K9 Kismet and they will make it happen.
K9 Kismet Adoption Application-https://k9kismet.org/forms/ 

Me in a nutshell:

Likes: Chew toys (loves stuffed animals), food/treats, car rides, hiking, and being around people in general.

Behavior: Grew up with a husky and is comfortable around other dogs, but needs to be introduced slowly. She likes to be queen bee and can be dominant. She has been known to bark and react to to other dogs who have lunged or showed aggression toward her. She is most comfortable around calm and older dogs. Has never been introduced to cats, but does extremely well around children especially when they are climbing all over her. 
Extremely scared of fireworks or other loud noises.

Skills: Knows basic commands (sit, stay, come, go lay down), house trained, pulls on walks at first due to excitement but walks by your side once calm, does well with grooming.

Medical: Has sunburn scabs on her nose (has had them since she was about 1 year old), not allergic to anything as far as we know, has a few chipped teeth from chewing toys/bones but that does not seem to cause her any discomfort.

Cinnamon is currently living in Victorville, CA. and is looking look for a temporary foster (12-14 months) or forever home in Los Angeles, Orange County, San Bernardino County, Riverside County or surrounding areas.

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Jonas is an adorable 3-month-old Chihuahua and blend who weighs approximately 5.4 pounds. Jonas initially is shy but once you offer him treats, he quickly displays his affectionate and playful nature.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most puppies, he may chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, plants, etc.
His adoption fee is $250. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccinations, Bravecto, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

animal.description:
Hello!  Thank you for checking out McMullen's listing.  Please read carefully for details on our adoption process:
•First, please note that we are unable to receive correspondence through Petfinder’s system.  Any messages sent through Petfinder or any buttons on this listing will unfortunately not reach us. If you’re interested in adopting please visit www.sanctuaryrescue.com and submit an adoption questionnaire under the forms section.
• Applications for puppies are open for two to three days in order to give ample opportunity to prospective adopters. At the end of this 48-72 hour period we will change the adoption listing to “Applications Closed”. At this point we will begin reviewing all applications received. Next, foster parents will contact approved applicants to set up a meet and greet. This can take up to 1 to 2 weeks.
• Once a dog is officially adopted we will remove its listing from Petfinder. So if this listing is gone, this dog has found its forever family and is no longer available.
• Since Covid lockdown orders, we have seen a massive increase in people interested in adopting dogs (yay!). This means each dog, especially puppies, receive multiple applications in the couple of days we have applications open. There is usually several applicants for one puppy. If it doesn’t work out this time, please understand this is not a personal judgement but likely a result of supply and demand. We encourage you to reapply in the future.

This lucky pup landed in the lap of Sanctuary Rescue with five siblings We are estimating them to be about nine weeks old. We never met mom or dad so breed and size is a pure guess. We estimate they'll be in the 40-50 pound range when full grown. These pups spend their time wrestling with the siblings, lounging around the house, playing tug and just enjoying some good old puppy fun. These pups are well socialized and love everyone they meet. They are young enough to learn about cats.

Foster mom says: "McMullen loves to carry a toy, enjoys wrestling with his brother and is a big fan of meeting new people."

McMullen's adoption fee is $295, which includes age-appropriate vaccinations, neuter, and microchip. If you would like to make this handsome pup a part of your family, please visit sanctuaryrescue.com and complete an adoption questionnaire under the “Forms” tab.

animal.description:
Cassie came to us from a shelter in TJ, where she had been kept in a kennel for more than 6 months, and she wasn't properly socialized as a puppy.  Once Cassie knows you, she is extremely loyal, gentle and sweet.  But, until then, she won't come too close.  She seems to prefer females to males (and that's usually due to past mistreatment), and it's something that can be remedied by the right male.  Cassie is affectionate and enjoys getting attention.  She doesn't have a mean bone in her body.  However, she needs to go to a quiet home (no children under 14), a home that appreciates her incredible disposition and is willing to walk her every day and spend time with her.  Cassie listens well, and hasn't had an accident in the house in days. Because of her gentle nature, she is probably good with cat (but we don't know for sure).  

Cassie is 2.5 years old, about 35 pounds, and has recently been spayed (that's why she has the cone on in her picture).  She has received all her shots, has been given deworm and flea medication.  If you would like to meet her in La Mesa, please email me and I'll send you an application (no calls please).

animal.description:
Meet Snuggles, a 6 month old Sheltie mix (Breed is just a guess) who weighs 20 lbs. This sweet girl is a bit on the shy and timid side, but she is learning to trust and is doing very well in her foster home. Snuggles is learning to walk on leash, but it is a work in progress. Sweet Snuggles needs another young and confident dog in her forever home to help her to gain her confidence. Since Snuggles is working on her leash training she will need a home with a fenced-in yard. Snuggles forever home should have someone at home a good portion of the day to continue her training, even after COVID. Due to Snuggles being shy and unsure, if there are children in her forever home they should be dog savvy and 10 years and up. Snuggles is not suited to apartment/condo living. Snuggles is doing well with her house training, does well in her crate, will be spayed this week, is up-to-date on vaccines and preventatives and eager to find a family to love!

The adoption fee for this dog is $350 which includes routine vetting and spay/neuter.

***Please note that our first step is submitting an application (it does not commit you in any way but allows us to discuss with you if you and the dog are a good fit). In addition, an important step in approving adoption applicants is to complete a vet check. Vetting of current and past pets is very important to us, thus we will be speaking with the vet(s) listed on your application to ensure that your current and previous pet(s) are kept up to date on vaccines (including rabies), spayed or neutered, maintained on appropriate monthly preventatives and examined annually by your vet.***

If you would like to meet Ally , please fill out our online application by clicking HERE and then email Kim at KLarimerLovepaws@gmail.com

****If you are viewing this on PETFINDER or other venues, please go to our website at www.lovepawspg.org to complete an application****

animal.description:
Forget Mega Millions... the only thing I want to win is your heart. My name is Cordelia! I am a gorgeous, 1 year old, 25lb., Heeler mix! I have energy for days and need a fenced in yard so I can run it off! I love to go on adventures in the car too! I haven’t had any issues with other dogs and would do best with older kids. I could live with cats if they are dog savvy and we do slow intros! I have mastered crate training but am still working on house training. Forget winning big with the lottery... I want to win big with my forever home! 


My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
Oscar is a sweet, gentle 10 year old, 15 lb Dachshund looking for a new home.  He was surrendered by a family that could not care for him anymore.  He suffers from hair loss which has left him almost completely hairless, but he does love his sweaters.  Oscar loves other dogs and is completely house trained and, as all Dachshunds do, loves a comfy couch.  He likes long walks and loves to say hi to everyone he meets.  Oscar’s foster can’t say enough great things about him.  He loves cuddles from his humans.  He is an awesome guy!!  He has had a dental, been neutered, and up to date on all his vaccinations - now all he needs is an amazing home that will love him forever -   If you are that family please fill out an application at

www.lowridersofthewest.org

Oscar is being fostered in Casper, Wyoming.

animal.description:
Callie, born , January 16, 2016 is a very pretty 34-pound, Blue Merle coloured Australian Cattle dog mix who is vaccinated, sterilized, and micro-chipped.
Very endearing with her beautiful blue eyes, this sweet girl wants an active adult home, with a fenced yard    Callie loves to go for walks, enjoys learning new things, and when tired is content to curl up at your feet with her chew-stick and snooze while you read or watch T.V .
Callie is an intelligent  girl who loves to learn so would enjoy the challenge of Rally Obedience or Doggie Agility  She works very hard for bits of chicken and cheese.
If you enjoy the active, intelligent Heeler dog breed, you will want to meet our Callie.
Visits to our Shelter are by appointment, only.
If you would like to meet Callie, please send a completed questionnaire to our email: ahspca@storm.ca Include a suggested day and time to meet Callie. We will confirm your appointment.
The SPCA of Western Quebec is located at --1658,chemin Pink, in the Aylmer Sector of the City of Gatineau..
Our visiting hours are Monday to Saturday from 11 A.M. to 5 P.M.
Please telephone us at 819-770-7722 should you need more information.

animal.description:
MEET REGINALD Reginald is a senior little dude that we just rescued due to severe neglect. This kid is in very bad shape. He is blind and severely matted. His dental disease is so bad that it hurts for him to chew. He has a significant heart murmur and is having mobility issues. We are working on getting this kid healthy and feeling good! We’ve got you Reggie. Reggie has already been to the vet and had full bloodwork and x-rays done. He got a long massaging bath on his first night along with a hair cut and can finally begin to heal. Reggie’s got a long road ahead of him for recovery but were committed to making sure Reginald doesn’t have to suffer another day of his life. We are looking for a hospice home for Reginald to give out the rest of his life. Please follow us on our Facebook page: Facebook.com/CastawayPetRescueInc for details on Reggie's journey. If you think you can help or might be the right home for this senior fellow, please email us at castawaypetrescue@gmail.com

If you are interested in adopting, please go to our website at www.castawaypetrescue.org and fill out an adoption application. An adoption counselor will contact you. Please bring any dogs, children, and decision makers to your appointment. Be prepared to adopt and take your new family member home that day if we have a match.

Please note that adoption counselors will only know of your interest if you submit an application. They do not see emails sent to the administration email account. The adoption counselor can answer your questions when they call after receiving your application. Please remember we are an all volunteer organization.

Minimum Adoption Donation is WAIVED (includes deworming, microchip with free registration, age appropriate vaccinations, spay if performed by our vet, 30 days of health insurance). Any donation above the minimum is appreciated

Foster Home Location: Champlin, MN

Our organization uses 24PetWatch microchips, which include free registration into the 24PetWatch pet recovery service. For more information visit www.24petwatch.com or call 1-866-597-2424.

To help reduce the financial and health risk, this dog also comes with 30 days of pre-paid pet health insurance. For more information please visit www.sheltercare.com or call 1-866-375-PETS.

animal.description:
We love our seniors!  Raine is a 10-year-old shihtzu who doesn't know how old she is.  She jumps on and off furniture and jumps for joy when it's time for dinner.  Raine has low vision and hearing but she can still hear you call her name and she can follow you inside or outside.  She gets along with all humans young and old (but only older respectful kids please, she's just 8 pounds) and she is fine with large and small dogs.  She is not much of a barker and sleeps peacefully in her crate at night. 
Raine has recently been spayed and had a hernia repair and a complete dental.  She has had senior bloodwork which shows she has a strong heart with no murmurs.   Raine doesn't seem to be totally housetrained but x-rays show no underlying issues.  She keeps her crate clean at night.     
Special needs dogs are special indeed and small dogs have many years of love to give.  If this is where your heart lies, apply for Raine at www.pounddogfounddog.org.

animal.description: Pepper is a lovely 2-year-old mixed-breed girl who currently weighs about 55 pounds. She came to SFAS as a stray. Here at the shelter, Pepper loves going on walks and receiving lots of treats! Pepper's adoption fee is $130. She is spayed and microchipped and has age-appropriate vaccinations. A licensing/microchip fee may apply. To meet Pepper or to be added to her waitlist, call (505) 983-4309 x 1610 and leave a voicemail message that includes the DOG'S NAME, plus YOUR NAME and A GOOD PHONE NUMBER - OR e-mail this information to adoption@sfhumanesociety.org. A scheduler will call you back within 48 hours to confirm your request. If you have other dogs at home, tell the scheduler you would like to bring them along for a Meet n' Greet. SFAS offers a variety of excellent training classes, seminars and Trainer Talks led by animal behavior professionals. These are $50 off for animals adopted from any shelter or rescue group! Due to current COVID-19 restrictions, classes and talks are all presented virtually using Zoom. For course descriptions, schedules and registration, visit https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/group-training-classes/ for classes and https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/special-seminars-and-workshops/ for seminars and Trainer Talks.

Trigger is 4 1/2 years old, male, about 75 lbs. He is a wonderful dog but he is, what we call, a LOT of dog! This just means he is a dog that needs to be able to get a LOT of exercise and if he doesn't get it he will get himself in trouble like he did chasing cattle. We were told by his previous owner that he is housetrained, crate-trained, good with other dogs, cats and children. He loves to play fetch, loves to RUN and is one big goofball!
DOG ADOPTION FEE is $100. This Adoption fee includes: mandatory spay/neuter which will be done before you can take your dog or puppy home with you; basic canine immunizations (DHPP-CPV & Bordatella Intranasal); de-wormings; one-year rabies vaccination if old enough; heartworm test if over five months old; microchip from 24-Pet Watch; certificate for free health examination at your participating veterinarian; and a goodie bag chocked full of information, toys, and more. (If a dog is sponsored or has a waived or lower fee, that info will be provided at the point of adoption to the approved adopter).
The first step is to our Adoption Application here: https://elmorehumane.org/adoption-application-online-form2.html .
IMPORTANT - we respond to your emailed applications and queries via email back to you. Please make sure you have either added our email (hselco@bellsouth.net) to your contact list or that you routinely check your SPAM folder for our response just to be safe. If we do not receive a timely response we simply move on to another applicant.
To learn more about us, visit our Website at: http://www.elmorehumane.org; Phone: (334) 567-3377 Fax: (334) 567-8774 E-mail: hselco@bellsouth.net

animal.description:
BE CAREFUL IF YOU CONTINUE READING YOU MAY FALL IN LOVE.ok we warned you! Extremely lovable, goofy, wiggly, and friend to everyone are just a few ways to describe Jerry a gorgeous medium black and white specked lab mix. He is extremely expressive, winking and smiling, his white-tipped tail never failing to wag. Much like Jerry the Mouse from the classic cartoon he loves to race around the yard at TOP SPEED then seconds later melt in your arms for a snuggle. Crate training is no problem for this guy, he sleeps 3-4 hours quietly in another room when you need to go out. You want to take him on family vacations? No problem, he walks well on a leash, is potty trained, and loves to be carried like a floppy baby. Be prepared for some love nibbles and a warm lap, because he can't get enough human attention. Who needs two eyes anyway! Jerry lives for adventure, confidently bounding through the forest picking up all the sticks, leaves, and pinecones carefully, not a care in the world. His endless energy outwits even the most difficult of walking paths, using his keen sense of smell and awareness to direct you back on the correct trail. He loves to remind you that multiple eyes are overrated anyway, it's more fun to wink good day to everyone you meet. Good with small and large dogs, Jerry has great manners and knows when to respect another dog's space, but playing for hours with willing participants. Don't pick up a toy and expect to put it away without him noticing! His indoor world revolves around nylabones, soft squeaky plushies, frisbees, and anything that you will let him have. Watch in amazement as he pounces on frisbee after frisbee, limbs flailing. He is also self-entertaining, throwing his toys in the air and catching them for his own amusement. To complement his responsible manner with other dogs and on the trails, Jerry is careful not to rip his prized possessions with his exceptionally soft mouth. He has captured many hearts with his incredibly good nature. If you would love a cuddle sesh and a wink, let him capture yours and get your application today!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Cedrick is a senior guy hoping to find a nice warm place to spend his golden years. He's 12 years-old, and is currently undergoing treatment for Heartworm Disease through our Survivor Program, which funds life-saving medical care for our homeless animals. Cedrick very much enjoys treats and cuddles, and would be so grateful to find a warm home where he can rest in peace on a soft bed or carpet.

If you've been thinking about adopting a senior dog that would be so grateful for a chance at living in a home and getting away from the noise and commotion of a shelter, then Cedrick might be the one for you. He's currently in a foster home, so if you'd like to visit him, just let us know so we can arrange for him to meet you!

animal.description:
Porkchop is a 7 year old neutered male lab mix who weighs 65 lbs. Porkchop was rescued from an overcrowded shelter after being found as a stray. Cast aside by his former people, this handsome boy is desperate for love! We don't know anything about his past, but we have promised him a future full of spoils. Porkchop is your typical happy-go-lucky lab boy who loves making new friends. He's been good with the dogs he has met and seems to enjoy their company. All Porkchop needs is some love, training, and some patience and he will undoubtedly flourish into the loyal companion he is meant to be. Please help us find this handsome boy the forever home he's been dreaming of!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description: This is Rusty, our approximately 3 year old mixed breed who came to us from Plumas County. Rusty came from a home in which he lived with his dog mom and dad as well as his litter mates. Unfortunately, Rusty was the runt of the crew and he was consistently picked on, making it not a safe home for him. Because of that, Rusty does take some time to warm up to people, but after a couple minutes is very accepting of pets. He will do best in a home where he is the only dog due to his past experiences. Other than that, Rusty is fairly easy going, although he does enjoy walks, so he would be very content with a yard, some walks, and some couch time at the end of the day. If you are interested in meeting Rusty, please fill out an application at www.highsierraanimalrescue.org. We do not discuss potential adoptions without an already submitted application.

animal.description:
Woof, woof!  My name is Brandy and I am an adorable beagle-mix puppy that needs to find a new place to live. (I am a mixed-breed girl with maybe a 'hint' of beagle... I don't know for sure.) I was born on November 24, 2020 in a shelter in the Carolinas.  I spent a few weeks in a foster home before making my way up to New Jersey with my mom, Buttermilk, and my 7 siblings.  I have been with Penny Angels Beagle Rescue for more than a month.  All of my siblings have been adopted into their forever homes, and my mom has a home waiting for her after she gets spayed.

I was recently spayed and can now start searching for a family that will love me.  I weigh 9.5 lbs. and will weigh more than 25 lbs. when I am full-grown.  I never met my dad and don’t know anything about him.  I have received 2 sets of puppy vaccinations and will need to receive 1-2 more sets of puppy vaccinations (1 month apart) as per your vet’s recommendations.  When I am old enough, you will need to bring me back to your vet for my rabies vaccination and anything else that I might need.  It is important to keep me up-to-date with my vaccinations and veterinary visits.  Since I am newly spayed, I should wear an e-collar to prevent me from chewing at my sutures.  My activity level will need to be restricted for approx. 7-10 days after my surgery to give my body time to heal.

I will need help with house-training in my new home; using a crate is one way to house-train me.  A crate is also a safe place for me to relax when you are not able to watch me.  At my age, I will need to potty approx. every 2 hours, but that time will increase as I get older and as you work with me.  Don’t leave me outside by myself, (and only take me outside for short periods of time in this cold weather).  If you decide to use pee-pads inside, you will have to teach me how to use them the right way.

Since I am still a puppy, I should be watched at all times when I am not crated so that I don’t get into any trouble.  Most puppies have a curious nature, so please be patient with me as you teach me right from wrong, (in a firm but gentle way).  Safe puppy toys will keep me occupied but I sure do hope that you will want to spend time with me.  I get along well with my siblings and would be fine with other dogs.  I can sometimes be quite vocal but that is just because I have a lot to say.  Do you have room in your heart and home for me?  Adopting a puppy is a lifetime commitment, so please adopt me ONLY IF you are willing to make that commitment!  

If you are interested in adopting Brandy, please fill out an application and submit it to Penny Angels Beagle Rescue.  Brandy’s adoption fee is $400, cash or check.  The application is available at www.pennyangelsbeaglerescue.com.  If your application is approved, you will be contacted via email or phone and an appointment will be scheduled (on a Saturday) for your adoption at PetSmart in Mays Landing, NJ.  Please wear a mask and follow social distancing guidelines.  If you have any questions, contact beagler534@comcast.net or emnase@aol.com, or call Penny Angels Beagle Rescue at 609-965-9476. Thank you!

animal.description:
Hey everyone! My name is Spud and I'm an 8 year old, 14lbs Chihuahua. 

- I was brought into the emergency room after getting hit by a car and was going to be euthanized until one of the vet tech's saw me and introduced me to the HIT Living Foundation. I was completely paralyzed from the waist down, and with the help of incredible vets, a very generous medical sponsor and my wonderful foster mama, I was able to regain full mobility in my legs!!! 

- That being said, I will need daily PT done by my adopter for about 10-15mins a day, to be able to maintain mobility in my legs. 

- I am a happy little gentleman. I am very alert and curious but also a little couch potato. 

- Even though I am very independent and enjoy to be on my own bed, I also LOVE cuddles. Especially, ear scratches!!

- My favorite things to do are sun bathing, playing with chew toys (so much so that I like to chew them until they are destroyed...oops), and ear scratches of course!

- Apart from my medical needs (PT and help peeing), I am veryyyy low maintenance. Give me a chew toy and I'll be good for the rest of the day. I am generally low on the energy scale, but definitely love the outdoors and my short walks. 

- In my foster home I live with 3 dogs and 2 cats. I was a little cautious and not so sure about the cats for the first couple of days but now I love playing with them. I am great with everyone, and might just take a couple of minutes to warm up to new people :)

- I definitely do not need a huge space but it would be great to have a patio, balcony or any area I can feel the wind and sun in my face!!

If you see me online I am still available for adoption! If you are interested in adopting me please fill out an application here: www.hitlivingfoundation.org/adoption-application, and email a video walkthrough of your home and yard to BOTH Nicole@hitlivingfoundation.org AND Marta@hitlivingfoundation.org. Your application will not be counted as valid without your video. You will hear back from us within a few days.

animal.description:
Don't bother buying once of those fancy schmancy mattresses--Dexter will give you the ins and outs of novel sleeping positions! We'd like to introduce you to Dexter! No, really, we want you to meet this derpy dude. 
He's around a year old and weighs about 70 pounds, but definitely a trim 70. He tries to be in tip top shape! 
Dexter is a bit shy when he first meets people, but if you're nice to him and maybe give him some treats (subtle, right?), he'll love you BIG time! Sometimes he thinks men can be particularly scary to meet, but he's really drawn to them once he realizes they are kind. And that they have treats. Treats help a ton. 
Dexter really is the sweetest, silliest boy. In fact, despite his size, Dexter strongly believes that your lap is his lap and will happily join you for a big slobbery kiss. 
Do you have another canine family member? Dexter has done great with small dogs and we think he can live with bigger dogs, too, but will need a slow and appropriate introduction to any doggy siblings. 
Because Dexter can be a bit shy, a low-activity, adult-only home (or a low-activity home with older kids) would be best for him. He'd also like a home without cats. He really just doesn't understand those creatures. 
Dexter is an athletic sort of pooch and needs a 6-foot privacy fence because he can be a little bit of an escape artist. He loves to play fetch with a ball, so keeping Dexter and his human(s) entertained is easy peasy. He's super treat motivated, too. (In case you haven't gotten the hint, the way to Dexter's heart is definitely through his stomach. And his stomach likes treats.) 
How about we get together to see if you're Dexter's forever person/family? Call/text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387. He's in the Kansas City metro, but transport is available to the right home. Let's do this!

animal.description:
Poor Toby was left at a high kill shelter by a family member because his owner was suffering from dementia and could no longer take care of him. As a 12-year old dog with a heart murmur and a serious eye infection, his adoption prospects were bleak. Then The Rescue Train pulled up and Toby hopped on!

His eye has almost completely healed and his heart condition is stable but due to the severity of his heart murmur, our cardiologist estimates his lifespan may only be 12 to 18 months. He is on heart and eye medication twice a day. Despite his condition, Toby is a happy boy who loves to eat, lay in the sun and curl up on anything soft. He is currently living in a foster home with two small, senior dogs who he gets along with. He can be reactive to other dogs on walks but his foster mom is working to redirect him. He is improving everyday is very responsive to treat training. Toby is housebroken but because he is on a diuretic, he also uses a pee pad.

---
If you are interested in adopting TOBY please fill out our adoption application on www.therescuetrain.org. Applications are required PRIOR to meeting one of our animals and are used to set up a safe and successful adoption. Please don't be shy and answer the questions thoroughly. To learn more about our entire process please visit www.therescuetrain.org and click on the "Adopt" page.

PLEASE NOTE: WE DO NOT OWN A FACILITY. Our animals are in private foster homes. If you are interested in adopting one of our animals please fill out our online application. Or check our mobile adoption schedule on our home page.

*APPLICANT MUST BE AT LEAST 21 YEARS OLD*
*APPLICANT MUST LIVE IN LOS ANGELES CITY*

INTERESTED IN ADOPTING?
PLEASE FILL OUT AN ADOPTION APPLICATION ON OUR WEBSITE: www.therescuetrain.org

animal.description:
Cuddles was picked up by animal control and turned into the shelter, where we got him.  He is a very friendly, sweet, calm dog  who loves getting attention.  Cuddles, like many of us, is a little overweight (due to eating too much or not getting enough exercise) and needs to lose a few pounds.  Despite that, he is very small and is one of the cutest dogs we've had.  He looks a lot like a gorgeous stuffed animal.  He definitely enjoys going on walks, but probably the walks need to be short at first, so he can build up his strength.

Cuddles needs to go to a home where there are no children under 10 (due to his very small size) and one where he will be walked a couple of times each day.  We don't know how he does around cats.  He is a very easy to take care of pup, but does need regular grooming (every 3 months)--otherwise his hair gets matted.  So, that's an expense any new home must consider.  Cuddles is hypo-allergenic, neutered, up to date on all vaccines, has been dewormed, microchipped and given flea medication.  We also got him professionally groomed on 1/26/21.  

If you want to meet him in La Mesa, email me and I'll send you an application (NO CALLS PLEASE).  Cuddles will get a lot of interest, so be sure to act quickly if you'd like to meet him.

animal.description:
Meet Pip -   this adorable little girl came to us at around 4-5 weeks old -  had been found dumped on the roadside in central KY -  a passer by was good enough to stop and pick her and her sibling up - falling in love and keeping the little boy.    They quickly took them to the local shelter in Johnson County who reached out to us immediately!

Pip has been with a wonderful foster who cared for her and got her all ready for her fur-ever home!

She is now 11 weeks old and ready for her own family!

Pip is happy, friendly, great with other dogs (has had a blast playing with her 2 foster brothers who are slightly larger at around 40lbs and her foster sister who is a little chi girl about her size.)

Pips breed is a bit of a mystery -  possible some whippet due to her long legs?   She has the most stunning brindle coloring and is a little thing - kinda delicate looking.   She will most likely remain a little girl - shouldn't be any more than 10-12 lbs at full grown.

Pip is a beautiful little thing and some lucky family will get to take her home!!

If interested, please apply on our website www.alldogscomefromheaven and click on the adoption application link at the top right on the page.

Meet and greet will be scheduled with approved application ONLY

Adoption fee is $325 and includes all age appropriate shots, worming, microchip with a lifetime registration and her spay (covered by us and scheduled with our vets) when she is between 24-26 weeks old!

animal.description:
PLEASE NOTE: Our little rescue has been inundated by inquiries about this puppy. We are thrilled--are responding as fast as we can--but it's slow-going. Until we catch up, we are putting additional inquiries on hold. So, please check back with us the second week in February, after Dora has arrived at which time we will have an even better idea of what would be the perfect adoption match for her. Thank you for understanding.
_________________

Here’s your chance to be the loving adopter of a very rare and unique dog!
Bora is a real Macedonian Shepherd who—along with her two little sisters—was “dumped” by the side of the road in Macedonia.
Unfortunately, her sisters came down with parvo (and one of them passed away, in spite of the care being given by the kind-hearted lady who rescued these pups).

But now Bora—who thankfully has remained healthy—is ready to come to the US, to find a new loving home.
(Her sister Becca will be coming in another month of two, at which time she—too—will be available for adoption.)

Bora is about four months old and is very playful, loving, and good with other dogs. We will need to have her spayed in a couple of months, but—in the meantime—we are looking for a potential adopter for her.
Bora would enjoy another doggie playmate and a fenced yard because she will be a BIG dog (and this breed needs exercise and enjoys being outside). She will need to attend puppy obedience class and she is still working on her housebreaking skills. So an adopter who is home much of the time, works out of his/her home (not just until Covid is resolved)--or who is retired—would be the best fit for Bora. She will grow to be a big girl (possibly between 75-90 pounds), and her adopter will need to do lots of brushing/grooming! Bora will be fully vetted prior to adoption and her adoption fee is $350.

Macedonian Shepherds are very loving and faithful to their family, they make great guard dogs (while not aggressive, their size and big “bark” is enough to scare most burglars away!)

Bora will be arriving in the US on February 7, and we welcome inquiries at this time. So if you feel your living situation would be a good fit for Bora, please write to us at: sylvialovesme@gmail.com and tell us about yourself—your daily schedule, about other members of the family, if you have other pets and/or a safely fenced yard (we don’t consider “invisible fencing” a safe way to contain a dog) etc.. Then, if we feel you would be a good match for Bora (and vice versa) we will send you an adoption application—after which time (if you live near Madison, Wi.) we can schedule a meet-and-greet along with a pre-adoption home visit.

animal.description:
Zoro came to us as a stray no one ever came looking for. Sad really as one look would tell you this is a dog pretty easy to describe. Zoro looks to be 2-3 years old and is about 70 lbs. Yes, his eyes are such a light blue they look almost white and he sees just fine. Zoro is very playful, good with female dogs but not male dogs. He walks well on a leash and seems to have a pretty laid back attitude. While a good dog this is not a dog for a first-time dog owner.
DOG ADOPTION FEE is $100. This Adoption fee includes: mandatory spay/neuter which will be done before you can take your dog or puppy home with you; basic canine immunizations (DHPP-CPV & Bordatella Intranasal); de-wormings; one-year rabies vaccination if old enough; heartworm test if over five months old; microchip from 24-Pet Watch; certificate for free health examination at your participating veterinarian; and a goodie bag chocked full of information, toys, and more. (If a dog is sponsored or has a waived or lower fee, that info will be provided at the point of adoption to the approved adopter).
The first step is to our Adoption Application here: https://elmorehumane.org/adoption-application-online-form2.html .
IMPORTANT - we respond to your emailed applications and queries via email back to you. Please make sure you have either added our email (hselco@bellsouth.net) to your contact list or that you routinely check your SPAM folder for our response just to be safe. If we do not receive a timely response we simply move on to another applicant.
To learn more about us, visit our Website at: http://www.elmorehumane.org; Phone: (334) 567-3377 Fax: (334) 567-8774 E-mail: hselco@bellsouth.net

animal.description: Meet Sebastian! One of our longest residents, Sebastian is looking for the perfect home! Sebastian is a sweet 5 year old Pit mix that prefers to hangout in our office rather that his kennel! He loves greeting everyone that comes through the lobby! Sebastian can look intimidating to some, but once you meet him he is the biggest baby! Sebastian loves his place toys, but the stuffing doesn't seem to last too long when he's around! He is a big goofball and always has a big smile on his face! Be careful though, he loves kisses! When Sebastian is done with you, you won't need a shower for a week! Sebastian is a strong boy, so he needs someone that can handle him and make sure he knows you are the boss. He would do well with older kid (13+) that can handle his size and strength. Sebastian prefers small dogs and would do okay with the right cat. If you are interested in meeting Sebastian, please fill out a questionnaire (either in person or online at gobroomecounty.com/shelter) and staff will contact those we would like to move forward with. If you have further questions about Sebastian, please call the shelter at (607)778-2493 or email us at muttsrus@broomecounty.us.

animal.description:
Prince is a four-year old male, about 6o lbs, and he came to us when his owner moved to an apartment. Prince is a very active boy, plays a bit too rough for young children but would be ok for teens and older. We were told he can jump out of a 4' fence. Exercise will be Prince's best friend so if you are looking for running or hiking buddy he would benefit greatly from that. A tired dog (as in one that gets the exercise it needs) is a more well-mannered dog and also less likely to want to escape to find fun elsewhere.
DOG ADOPTION FEE is $100. This Adoption fee includes: mandatory spay/neuter which will be done before you can take your dog or puppy home with you; basic canine immunizations (DHPP-CPV & Bordatella Intranasal); de-wormings; one-year rabies vaccination if old enough; heartworm test if over five months old; microchip from 24-Pet Watch; certificate for free health examination at your participating veterinarian; and a goodie bag chocked full of information, toys, and more. (If a dog is sponsored or has a waived or lower fee, that info will be provided at the point of adoption to the approved adopter).
The first step is to our Adoption Application here: https://elmorehumane.org/adoption-application-online-form2.html .
IMPORTANT - we respond to your emailed applications and queries via email back to you. Please make sure you have either added our email (hselco@bellsouth.net) to your contact list or that you routinely check your SPAM folder for our response just to be safe. If we do not receive a timely response we simply move on to another applicant.
To learn more about us, visit our Website at: http://www.elmorehumane.org; Phone: (334) 567-3377 Fax: (334) 567-8774 E-mail: hselco@bellsouth.net

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please contact Jenny Cope (giveadogahome@live.com) for more information about this pet.

Be sure to read ALL information provided.

A PET IS FOR LIFE -
THINK ABOUT THE INVESTMENT!

MACEY came to the rescue with her 4 puppies, Stacey, Lacey, Kacey-boy and Tracey. She was in bad shape, very thin, hair loss around her neck where it appears she had been tied up and the rope of collar wore on her neck, she had an extremely thin coat, was itching and had demodex mange. She was very protective over her pups and took time to allow anyone near her. However, she learned to trust and grew into a beautiful soul who was just trying to survive and keep her pups alive and safe.

Please do NOT submit an application if you do not have a lifestyle that the dog needs to be happy and healthy.

Macey is spayed, rabies, core vaccines, heartworm, tick disease tested, de-wormed, monthly preventatives and microchipped. At the time of her spay surgery on 13 January 2021, she weighed around 38.00 pounds and has an estimated date of birth 11 January 2020.
We cannot say for sure what breed she is, so we expect families to do their own research on her look and size and decide what breed you think she is and if you have the lifestyle suitable for her needs.

Macey has been at the rescue with her with her pups in the house and whilst at first she was very protective of her pups and the area she was in she has adjusted great over the months and has learnt to play and run and hang out among the other dogs. She is still VERY attached to her pups and they are all constantly playing together and snuggling up on the dog beds together. When new dogs have come in Macey has got a bit barky with them, but I feel this is just because of what she has gone through and she still has her protective feelings over her pups. She has never been aggressive, just wants everyone to know it is her space.

At the vets she was great, she was friendly with everyone she met and happily went back with the vet staff for her spay surgery. She is great at alerting to noises and will go to the part of fence where she heard the noise, and does generally come in when called. She is a very sweet girl, who will reach out with her paw for attention. Her hair has started to grown back and although not thick, it will most likely take a few seasons for that to come through as it should.

Macey would benefit from an active family, one that understands she is going to need time and patience to transition, she is going to miss her pups, but she is still young and I am sure will adapt to an active lifestyle and loving home. She is very affectionate and loves to snuggle and does gently jump up for her ears to be scratched but nothing that is imposing.

She needs a family that will work with her on training and understanding the new rules of her home and family and ensure she gets all the love, structure and routine she needs and deserves.
She does use the dog door to go out and play, but if she is inside she will use the pee pads to do her business so house training should be expected and planned.

We do not know how she will be around cats or livestock so families are expected to be prepared to work through potential problems and provide a safe and happy living environment for all animals, and humans.

More pictures and possible video's can be found on his page on the rescue website.

You MUST understand that dogs need time to decompress and adapt to their new environment and home. It is a HUGE transition they make from the kill shelter, being vetted, on transport for 3 days and arriving in Maine where the temperature and such is very different to what they have only known. In rescue there is what is known as the "3 Point Rule" Days 1-3 your dog is stressed, anxious, confused as to where they are now. Weeks 1-3 your dog is adjusting, settling in, learning things. At the 3 month point, your dog understands they are home, and have built up a trusting relationship where they feel loved and secure.

All dogs are fed Rachael Ray Nutrish PEAK Natural Dry Dog Food, Grain Free Western Grasslands Recipe with Bison. Rachael Ray Nutrish Peak Dog Food receives the Dog Food Advisor's second-highest tier rating of 4.5 stars.

MACEY is available for adoption for an adoption fee of $550

This fee is not negotiable and is used to cover the rescue costs of pulling, vetting, health certificate, transport from Texas to Maine, monthly preventatives, supplements, food, general day to day cost of running a brick and mortar rescue and anything else that is needed. Canadian adopters need to know that customs charge 15% taxes when entering into Canada.

Due to borders being closed, it is up to families to call the US and Canadian borders to find the current details on border crossing. Animal Welfare is deemed essential in the US, but quarantine rules entering back into Canada must be followed.

If you feel that you have the heart and home to give this precious soul a wonderful life, please go to our website, under the ADOPTION INFO tab, complete, then submit the APPLICATION. Our process takes around 1-2 days, and ensuring your references are aware that we will be calling, could speed up the process. Once you have been approved, we discuss any questions in regards to the dog you are wanting to adopt, then you complete and submit the contract, make payment and then we can work out the pick up / transport arrangements.

Please do NOT submit an application if you are not looking to take home a new best friend within the next few weeks.

https://www.giveadogahome-sanantonio.org/forms/form?formid=5838

ALL Dogs are LOCATED AT THE RESCUE IN SEBEC, MAINE. We post in various states along the east coast and Canada where we have had lots of successful adoptions to enable more exposure for these beautiful saved souls. Families will need to be prepared to travel to the rescue to meet and take home their new best friend. Sebec is located just outside the towns of Dover-Foxcroft and Milo (approx 8 miles) and approx 45 miles from Bangor. There are also lots of hotels, motels, pet friendly accommodations and wonderful camp-sites for the more adventurous families and what a great way to get to know your new best friend.

Click here to watch a video of MACEY.

A PET IS FOR LIFE -
THINK ABOUT THE INVESTMENT!

NOQRAH was saved by a small rescue based in Kabul, Afghanistan. She was saved from the streets, neglected and starving to death. Once she was deemed healthy, Noqrah and her friend Khushi

were flow into the US where they waited in a boarding facility for transport up to Maine. They arrived at GaDaH on 25th January 2021.

Noqrah is scheduled for spay surgery on 24 February 2021, she has current rabies, core vaccines, de-wormed, heartworm and tick disease tested negative, monthly preventatives and microchipped. At the time of her export/import examination she weighed she weighed around 20.00 pounds and has an estimated date of birth 15 July 2020.

We cannot say for sure what breed she is, so we expect families to do their own research on her look and size and decide what breed you think she is and if you have the lifestyle suitable for her needs.

For all that this sweet girl has been through, she is doing amazing, to think just over a week ago she was in Afghanistan, endured 48 hours traveling to US, then in a boarding facility for a few days and then driven for 1.5 days up to Maine and is a happy-go-lucky girl.

Noqrah is all puppy, she is bouncing around so excited she doesn't know what to do. She loves being with all the dogs and is enjoying charging around outside chasing and playing.

She has not had any training and so housetraining as well as obedience should be expected and planned for. Noqrah can be possessive with her food, toys and treats, this is most likely due to many reasons, the main ones being she had been found starving and she is not used to sharing, so where other animals are concerned supervision should be carried out and feeding not close to each other. She is not aggressive just doesn't want to share and will snap at a dog trying to get what she has. Since she is young, this is easily worked on and whilst here at the rescue she is learning with the other rescue and house pack that this behaviour is not needed.

We are looking for a family that go on hikes, walks, treks, adventures, to the beach, the lake, anywhere and everywhere that is fun and would give this beauty a wonderful fun filled life. She is going to need training, she is not fully house-trained, but does use pee-pads if they are put down - she just needs to learn to let her family know she needs to go outside. Noqrah
is going to be a medium/large high energy dog and so she needs an active family who already have an adventurous and active lifestyle they can incorporate her into. She is a smart girl and so training and continued mental stimulation is also very important to make sure she gets the healthy, both physical and mental lifestyle that she needs and deserves.

animal.description:
Looks like: Chihuahua-Terrier Mix
Male, 12 years old, about 9 pounds

Dollar came to us with his mom, Mama Jazzy. Like her, he's on the shy side, but he's definitely the more outgoing of the two, and has showed interest in playing with other small dogs. Dollar is a picky eater, since he's used to being fed table scraps, though he can sometimes be enticed to eat wet dog food. He's also unused to wearing a leash, collar, or harness, due to having always remained at home with his guardian. Despite this, he is tolerant of being outfitted and being on leash so he just needs some guidance. 

Dollar is suffering from congestive heart failure, and after his guardian passed away, his guardian's family members were unable to afford his medical care. Thankfully POMDR is starting him on meds that can help him live a normal life and we are happy to help this great little guy find a new family to entertain.

animal.description:
Looks like: Poodle
Female, 14 years old, 7 pounds

Barbee is such a loving and sweet girl. She loves attention and now that the weather is getting colder, she is pumped to be cuddled. Barbee is hard of hearing and cannot hear verbal commands, taking visual cues instead. Barbee is a sweet, gentle soul that has transitional and separation anxiety. She will whine while riding in the car and is going to have a hard time adjusting to her forever home. She will need weeks to settle in and be very sad and anxious, preventing herself from truly settling in until completely familiar. 

She looks amazing for her age, both with her health and beauty. She has an old leg injury that she favors. Part of it is a luxated knee cap on her left hind leg and while she will stand with weight on all 4 limbs, she usually walks holding that leg up. Despite her leg, Barbee lives for her walks. Even when overwhelmed with anxiety, she cheers up for an explorative walk. Her future person should be able to take her on a couple walks a day. 

Barbee comes to us because her guardian could no longer take care of her. She has been with her guardian her entire life, so these changes have been very tough on her. She barks and whines when she is sitting in a new place because she is not happy with change. We are sure she will blossom in a loving and patient home though as she is an absolute doll and after a long adjustment, she will make a perfect companion for the right person.
animal.name: Barbee

He is friendly to all he meets, is non-destructive in the home and thoroughly enjoys car rides. He is not cat-safe, so he needs a cat-free home. Because he  humps when he’s too excited, we believe he isn’t suited to be around toddlers and young ones as he may create a fall risk. He is quite simply a goofy, affectionate guy just waiting for his new family!

animal.description: I'M CURRENTLY ON HOLD, PENDING AN ADOPTION APPOINTMENT! Kevin is a handsome 6-month-old mixed-breed guy who currently weighs about 51 pounds. He came to SFAS as a stray in rough shape but thanks to our veterinary team they were able to help him heal and get him back into good shape. Now he is now ready to find a loving family to call his own. Here at the shelter Kevin has become a staff favorite and has been very affectionate with humans and enjoys going walks. Kevin's adoption fee is $130. He is neutered and microchipped and has age-appropriate vaccinations. A licensing/microchip fee may apply. To meet Kevin or to be added to his waitlist, call (505) 983-4309 x 1610 and leave a voicemail message that includes the DOG'S NAME, plus YOUR NAME and A PHONE NUMBER - OR e-mail this information to adoption@sfhumanesociety.org. A scheduler will call you back within 48 hours to confirm your request. If you have other dogs at home, tell the scheduler you would like to bring them along for a Meet n' Greet. SFAS offers a variety of excellent training classes, seminars and Trainer Talks led by animal behavior professionals. These are $50 off for animals adopted from any shelter or rescue group! Due to current COVID-19 restrictions, classes and talks are all presented virtually using Zoom. For course descriptions, schedules and registration, visit https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/group-training-classes/ for classes and https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/special-seminars-and-workshops/ for seminars and Trainer Talks.

animal.description:
Sophie just loves being around people! Pet her and cuddle with her, and she doesn't need much more. She's never lived with other animals or kids, so we will learn more about that as she's with us longer. She's always had a fenced yard to play in, so she hasn't been on a leash much - you can hardly tell. She's a little rusty (pulls some), but will figure it out in no time! When alone during the day, she was reported to be housebroken and she didn't get into any trouble. Some of her favorite things are spending time with people and playing games like fetch and chase! 

Sophie has a history of allergic skin disease or atopic dermatitis, which has been successfully treated/managed by her previous owners and veterinarian. Sophie has not displayed any signs of allergic skin disease yet while at HSDC (her coat is beautiful and shiny!) but please be aware that atopic dermatitis is a life-long condition that commonly requires regular therapy with a full service veterinarian. Of course, that's an extra expense to consider (a small price to pay for unconditional love?).

animal.description:
This 3 year old Husky/Malamute is sooooo sweet. He was kept on a tie out in trailer park for his young life and while his owner deeply loved him, they knew that that lifestyle wasn’t fair to Zuma. They admitted that they didn’t know how to train him and as a result Zuma needs some training. He chews inappropriately and is destructive if he is frustrated and unsupervised. He is very dog social and would love a doggy playmate, but will chase cats and livestock. He is scared of thunder, vacuums and loud noises. He is great with kids and loves to play. He will bark/alert at passing cars, people, bikes and livestock.

We think Zuma will make an amazing family dog for folks who don’t mind putting a little work into some training. He would be fine living in town or in the country.  This big fluffy guy definitely needs some work learning to take food gently and not jumping. When he gets really riled up and wants to play he can get a bit mouthy, but that behavior isn’t persistent and is easily redirected. Zuma is just a chunky guy who needs some structure, enrichment and proper exercise.

If Zuma sounds like the one you’ve been looking for, don’t hesitate to email us ,or give us a call, and see if you guys have chemistry!

Dogs: Yes

Cats:No

animal.description: Meet Jackson! Jackson is a 6 year old Boxer mix that is looking for a lap to sit on and a hand to be pet with! Jackson loves your company and can't get enough of it! Jackson is such a happy boy despite the rough start he had in life! He came to us as a walking skeleton that was very concerned with where his next meal was coming from. If you are having a bad day, Jackson will fix it with his magic cuddles and kisses! If you are interested in meeting Jackson, please fill out a questionnaire (either in person or online at gobroomecounty.com/shelter) and staff will contact those we would like to move forward with. DOG'S DESCRIPTION

Courtesy Posting

waldocrum@gmail.com

Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.

Adoption fees cover basic vetting, spay/neuter surgery (for dogs over 6 months old), rabies, distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing, monthly heartworm prevention and monthly flea/tick prevention (while the animal is in our care), and transport costs from high-kill shelter. Please note that on average, K-9 Lifesavers spend significantly more on each dog than their adoption fee. Adoption fee for HW positive dog also covers heartworm treatment at our partner vets.

Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org

Sponsor Me! Make a tax-deductible donation today by visiting us at http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/ . Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support!

For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.

animal.description:
Meet our girl Ari aka “Weenie” because frankly she is a completely endearing wimp. Ari is a Shepard/Husky/Bully blend and is as gorgeous as she is intelligent. She is a bit prone to environmental stress and can be a nervous nelly when she feels out of her comfort zone. She tends to tuck herself away and avoid sounds and people that she doesn’t immediately recognize, but she comes around quick and is eager to please. She is all about the appeasing behavior – she wants you to love her, play with her and be kind to her. She is gentle and fun, with tons of personality that she makes you work a little to discover – but boy is it worth it!

Ari’s life changed when her owners of three years had a baby. Ari was nervous around the baby and tried to avoid it, but as the baby aged Ari wasn’t able to have separate space and it escalated her discomfort. We think that she struggled with having no control over when the child entered her personal bubble. She does excellent with people who give her time to come to them, and obviously that isn’t a baby’s strong suit. It was devastating for her family to have to give her up in the hopes of finding her a situation that was more conducive to her happiness. She came from a home that loved her so very much, but they did what they felt they had to do for her.

Ari grew up with cats in the home and played with the dogs of family friends. She would likely love to have an animal buddy or two in her life who were easy going and social. She can be the most nervous around men, but does well as soon as she learns they have a safe and gentle demeanor. Confidence building and exposure to new things in her next home will really help her become more sure-footed. She is ready to get out of here and into a new family.

Cats: Yes

Dogs: Probably

Kids: 10+, dog-savvy

animal.description: Why hello there, I'm a handsome boy named Bali currently seeking my pawfect forever match. My best fit would be a confident and experienced human friend that can understand my past and allow me patience as well as help me with confidence building. Unfortunately, I have only ever lived outside in my past, but from now on, I am seeking a home where I can stay safely indoors and become a part of my human's everyday life. It will take me time to warm up in my new home, become accustom to the ways of the house and I would do best in one that is not very busy with visitors or guests, so that I do not become overwhelmed. I think I would very much like as much as benefit from having a confident, friendly, and social dog companion in my new home to help show me the ropes. A relationship of structure, routine and guidance would give me the opportunity to gain my own confidence and help me become the best boy that I can be. Please contact my friends at HALO if you think we would be a good fit and they can set up an appointment for us to meet each other!

animal.description:
A SMART & HANDSOME FRIEND:  5 years old / 70 lbs.

Hello!  My name is Chi-Chi!  I had a home, but one of the other dogs in the home was being aggressive toward me without provocation, so it is best that I find another family to love.  Mostly Mutts is helping me do just that!

• OTHER DOGS/CATS/KIDS:  Though one of the dogs in my previous home did not like me, I got along well with the other dogs and enjoyed playing with them a bit – though I didn’t snuggle up with them.  There was also an older dog in the home that could be grumpy, so I just gave him his space.  I think I would be fine as an only dog or with another friendly dog in my new home.  So, if you have a nice dog already, let’s meet / I got along with the kitties in my former home, so if you have a dog-friendly kitty, let’s meet / I’ve not met kids at Mostly Mutts, but my previous owner reports I was good with the kids I met while with them, though I’m a big dog and occasionally goofy so I could bump younger kids over, so let’s meet and best no very young kids that I may bump over!

• PERSONALITY/ENERGY LEVEL:  I am a friendly guy who loves my people. I’m described as sweet, mild-mannered and mostly calm – though I do get excited when getting ready for a walk and at mealtime, yummy!  I enjoy leisurely hang out on the couch, playing a bit or going for a walk as I’m a go with the flow fellow. I look forward to being someone’s great companion / My energy level is 4-6.

• SKILLS/CRATE/POTTY:  I completed an obedience class in February of 2020, and reportedly know the following commands: ‘sit’, ‘stay’, ‘down’, ‘wait’, ‘look’ and ‘come’.  My former family had me ‘sit’ and ‘wait’ at doors until released so I would not rush out a door.  I did the same before coming in if it’s wet and I need to have my paws cleaned.  I’m a smart guy! / I did not need to be crated in my former home, though I would go in and out of it on my own to take a nap or chew a bone / My former owner reports that I had great potty habits, so hopefully that will be the case in my new home too. 

• LIKES/DISLIKES:  I like leisurely walks sniffing interesting things along the way, spending time with my people, and chewing Nyla bones.  I also enjoy being outside a bit listening to the sounds of the neighborhood and keeping an eye on things / I didn’t like the stress/negative energy from the dog in my former home picking on me.  I can get overheated on hot Georgia days when on walks, so just a short walk when it’s really hot will do.  I would not like it if I did not get the love and attention all doggies deserve!   

• MEDICAL:   I'm current on vaccinations, micro-chipped and neutered.   I am on prescriptive low-fat dog food for digestive care right now as sometimes I got tummy aches and this type of food is helpful.  I’m gradually transitioning to a non-prescription low-fat food for digestive health – we have to see how that goes.  

I am looking for a loving family to give me a wonderful home!  My adoption fee is $299.00, and I’m located in Kennesaw, Ga.
animal.name: Chi Chi

animal.description:
Petey oh Petey.. what a sweetheart... He is basically a snuggle bug and is super friendly with all ages. He currently resides with his foster family and aviary friends. He sleeps through the night with his humans and wakes up mid morning. He has had no accidents in the middle of the night, or in the house for that matter -  this sweet boy is fully housebroken. 

His week day job is Supervisor of the House. While his fosters work and school, he visits each one to make sure every thing is in order. He keeps himself busy inside, likes to run around the yard, and take naps when he tires himself out. 

Do you like hiking? Walks? Jogging? Meet your outdoor partner here. He's been getting 3-4 mile jogs at the park a day and he loves it. He enjoys playing with other dogs and especially playing fetch with his humans. He is an active dog and would love to join an active family. It would be a bonus if he would have another active fur sibling to live with. 

He is basically all around fun to be with and a well mannered guy. He is deaf but that doesn't hinder him in any way. He can hear very high pitches. We will have him evaluated by a vet and will have more information soon.

Will you give this sweet boy a 2nd chance with a forever home, safe and loved? 
Adoption Fee: $400
San Francisco Bay Area adoption only.
If you would like to meet Petey, please apply at http://www.lovewoof.org/our-animals: . 

Adoption Process:
Once an adoption counselor receives and approves your application, they will contact you (only if you match the animal's needs) to set up an appointment to meet the dog you applied for and/or any of the other dogs in the rescue. If the dog you applied for is not a good match for your particular situation, there might be others that are better matches.

Adoption Fees:
Adoption fees allow WOOF Animal Rescue to continue to provide care and medical treatment (including spay/neuter services) for dogs while we look for their forever homes. The fees also helps cover the ongoing costs of caring for less adoptable dogs that require longer stays in the rescue, or more advanced medical treatment before finding their forever homes.

WOOF Animal Rescue, in Fremont CA, does not have a shelter, all of our dogs are raised in foster homes. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up to date on vaccinations and rabies shots appropriate for their age, dewormed and microchipped.

Due to long work hours she doesn't have the time that Luna needs, as she is still a pup and has loads of energy. Luna gets along with other dogs that don't mind her exuberance. She would LOVE to be in an active home that is willing to throw a ball for her and that can match her energy level.
She is leashed trained, but pulls, she is house and crate trained. She would benefit from a refresher course in basic obedience. She has lived with kids before and while she is not aggressive towards them she does forget her manners and size so little ones who are not steady on their feet won't be the best fit.

*The pet you are viewing is a rescued pet which is most often from an animal control facility and does not come with a pedigree. The breed(s) listed are our best guess and are in no way guaranteed. Sometimes the pets appear to be a particular breed(s) in the pictures we receive from our rescue partners and when they arrive we are surprised to see an entirely different breed(s) in person! If you choose to DNA test your adopted pet, test results may vary from company to company and our breed guess may not be reflected in those results as it is just that, our best guess. It is with deep longing that we wish there was a breed called "cute" as we believe all of our dogs would fall under this new breed classification!

animal.description:
This animal is not available to foster. SAVE is looking for forever homes for our animals.

Please note: Due to high volume email inquiries will not be returned. Please go to our website, complete an online application (if you haven't already) and indicate which animal(s) you are interested in. Once approved, you will be contacted to schedule an adoption appointment. Kindly call the shelter if you have any questions. 

**Please note: puppies will not be adopted into homes without prior puppy experience nor to anyone living outside of New Jersey. No exceptions will be made.**

Hi, I'm Watson! I came to SAVE with my siblings all the way from Navajo Nation in Arizona. There, resources are lacking and my litter mates and I went without vet care until arriving at SAVE. If we had not been rescued by a Good Samaritan, we would never have known the safety, security and love that a home can provide. We really aren't sure what mix of breeds me and my siblings are... in fact, one of SAVE's amazing volunteers treated my sister to a DNA test so that we can find out. Where I come from, most dogs are a mix of lots of different breeds, so we are excited to find out! Before arriving at SAVE, I had not had a variety of exposure to new people, sights, or smells. While I've been at SAVE, I've been learning how much fun it is to play with people and experience new things. I'll need a family who has the patience to give me the time to learn to love and trust them. The staff at SAVE consider me a medium energy dog. I do love to explore and would love to be with an active family. I am really smart and food motivated, so with consistency and patience, I should be able to quickly master training and tricks. I would be happy to live with other dogs and maybe even a cat (although I would probably chase them a bit). I would do best in a home with children 14 and older. If you have puppy raising experience and are looking for an awesome, active dog, I'm your guy!

For more information please call SAVE at 609-309-5214.
 Primary Color: Tan Secondary Color: White Weight: 14.125lbs Age: 0yrs 3mths 3wks Animal has been Neutered
