animal.description:
Sweet Lila was brought to us on January 13th after spending over 2 years at a shelter in Arkansas. She is a 5 year old Labrador retriever mix, and after a rough start in Arkansas, is ready to find her forever home. She is spayed, microchipped and up to date on all vaccines. 

Lila has made such tremendous progress since being here and very much enjoys her newfound luxuries of couches and cuddles. She is a very fast learner and eager to please; Lila came to us not knowing any commands or trainings, and already knows how to sit, walks great on a leash, and is house trained. Because of her history, she has anxiety being home alone and will need to be crated when her humans leave. She loves to be in her crate during the day with the door open, and is working on liking her crate at night too. She is very affectionate towards people but can take time to warm up to other dogs, so Lila is hoping to find a home where she is able to be the only dog -- she's definitely awesome enough to handle that. Lila is a sucker for belly rubs, snuggles, and simply loves to be in presence of her people.

Lila is currently being treated for heartworm and is looking for a home where she can relax until she is all better! Costs for the treatment are paid for by Hearts of Hope. Her adopter would need to bring her for her final treatments in February and keep her activity low until her treatment is completed.

Interested? This little girl is so full of love and is ready to be with her forever family. Her adoption fee is $250 and you can apply for her on our website at: https://rescueofhope.com/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Meet Rupert... A Good Samaritan reached out to us for help for this little guy and his siblings. Thankfully, we were finally able to secure fosters after they were kinda just the neighborhood pups their whole lives. We honestly have no idea what their breed is. They have long bodies and short little legs like a dachshund. Some have terrier looking heads and some kinda favor a Bulldog. Whatever the mix it’s a cute one. They were born 8/24/20. Being 5 months old they won’t grow much more we believe. Rupert is now 17.6 lbs. We think he will top out around 20 lbs likely. They are sweet pups but haven’t had much socialization with anyone besides the lady that’s been caring for them until they came into our care. Rupert is the most timid of the litter. He is slowly but surely coming stunned with his foster mom.  He is starting to realize the good life and being indoors isn’t so bad. He’s great with all the animals in his foster home and he is trusting his foster mom more daily. He’s starting to ask for human attention on his own and loving it. He’s been started on house and kennel training and is doing well. He’s learning all about sleeping in the bed and learning to cuddle. He will be timid at first in a new situation and will need a little extra patience at first. Rupert is utd, dewormed and neutered. 

All dogs have a $175 adoption fee which includes vet check, age appropriate shots (atleast 2 sets for puppies), dewormer, heartworm test (if over 6 months), rabies (if atleast 16 weeks) and spay/neuter! Puppies will be altered before adoption. All rescues and shelters practice pediatric spay and neuter. This is essential in our rescue efforts and it is a policy that we will stick by. All dogs over 8 weeks and 2 pounds will be altered before adoption. There are no exceptions to this rule on all healthy and adoptable dogs. 

Puppies/Dogs that are not available for adoption due to vetting not being complete can be reserved with an approved application and a non refundable $50 deposit. This deposit is applied to your adoption fee and the remaining $125 is due at pick up.

Wags and Whiskers is an all-volunteer rescue. We also have full-time jobs and Families. We will try to answer all questions and applications in a timely manner. Please be patient and bear with us . Do not contact Parkway Animal Hospital as they are a vet clinic and can not answer questions on behalf of Wags and Whiskers. All questions and comments must go directly through the rescue. Thank you for your understanding.

ADOPTION APPLICATION

animal.description:
If you are looking for an extremely loyal, ride or die, best friend in the whole wide world then Liliana is the girl for you. This extremely brilliant, young, vivacious, adorable little girl loves to do many things but she will always be her happiest hanging out with you just doing whatever you're doing. Liliana loves car rides, loves to play with toys and other dogs (no cats). She really loves to play fetch with a ball launcher and she loves to take long walks. She especially loves to go on hikes out in nature where she can contemplate life and get some fresh air. Liliana is also more than happy to help you with your chores. She even likes to help with laundry and is really great at sorting socks. Liliana also really loves to snuggle and doesn't think much about the idea of personal space. She makes the most adorable little grunts and groans like a little piglet when being loved on and has the cutest pink piggy nose. Liliana is a very muscular but small girl and weighs 46 pounds. Liliana does have some food allergies and will need to eat special dog food. She is also very food driven and is one super smart cookie so we are currently working on learning kitchen boundaries to prevent her from getting into something she shouldn't be eating. She's crate trained and potty trained.

Adoption fee of $150 includes spay, microchip, vaccines, deworming, heartworm testing, and heartworm/flea/tick prevention

animal.description: This is Max. He is a BIG sweetheart (approx 95lbs) with a troubled past. He came to us like a wild child Tasmanian devil and has spent the last 4 weeks learning to be a sweet inside dog and that humans can be pretty cool. He is good with other dogs (I have 4 small and large) but I believe he would be best suited with a large mature female dog that would take him under her wing. He is three years old and is plenty playful once he is comfortable in his environment. He even lets me clean his paws when he comes inside! He needs lots of reassurance and wants to be at least within eyesight of his person, if not touching them with a paw. He is crated at night from 10p-5am and will alert if he has to go out before then. He does best with females and seems afraid of big men. He has gained weight since we took him in and is fed 2x a day but is VERY food aggressive with other pets. He is not neutered as he is heartworm positive and on medication so he does mark in the house sometimes and wears a belly band. He has been on car/truck rides and does need a divider up unless you want him to drive . He is going to be the most loving, loyal friend to a lucky person

animal.description: As her foster, I really hate writing this bio. Queenie could have been available for adoption already, but knowing what an awesome dog she is, it'll be no time before she has people begging her to choose them and I suppose I just wanted to be selfish and have more time with her. She was in such dire condition when we first got her that she and her brother started having seizures and it did not look good -- but this little lady has never met an obstacle she can't overcome. So she and her brother fought and learned and grew and after a few months, Queenie looked like the royalty she was named for. This dog is funny and fun, she is sweet and so affectionate, she has impeccable dog body language skills. She likes to find her voice sometimes and even her bark is melodic. She loves to play fetch and hide and seek. She loves to cuddle with the other dogs and go on car rides. She prefers a dog bed with a soft blanket to human furniture and her curiosity and excitement about everything is contagious. Even when she is being a total puppy she is a total delight. This dog can do just about anything. While she can find joy in most situations, her dream home would have another dog that wants a companion, people that want to continue her training (this one could rock agility/fast CAT/dock diving), adventures, and a desire to let Queenie's personality shine. She is fully vetted, crate/house/leash trained. She is about 8 months old, 40lbs, a beautiful brindle petite boxer mix (yep, complete with barrel chest and docked tail). She likes everyone and everything but with other pets and people, she expects respect -- she isn't interested in anything "alpha" because at this point in evolution, that's just rude. Her adoption fee is $150. After completing the application with references, if we feel you might be a good fit for Q, we will update you on your application and the process. As a small rescue run entirely by volunteers, we thank you in advance for your patience on our response to inquiries.
animal.name: Queenie

animal.description:
Meet Ricky... A Good Samaritan reached out to us for help for this little guy and his siblings. Thankfully, we were finally able to secure fosters after they were kinda just the neighborhood pups their whole lives. We honestly have no idea what their breed is. They have long bodies and short little legs like a dachshund. Some have terrier looking heads and some kinda favor a Bulldog. Whatever the mix it’s a cute one. They were born 8/24/20. Being 5 months old they won’t grow much more we believe. Ricky is now 18.8 lbs. We think he will top out around 20 lbs likely. They are sweet pups but haven’t had much socialization with anyone besides the lady that’s been caring for them until they came into our care. Ricky is already enjoying the good life and being indoors. He’s great with all the animals in his foster home and he loves his foster mom. He’s been started on house and kennel training and is doing well. He’s learning all about sleeping in the bed and learning to cuddle. He likely will be a little timid at first in a new situation but will open up quickly. Ricky is utd, dewormed and neutered. 

All dogs have a $175 adoption fee which includes vet check, age appropriate shots (atleast 2 sets for puppies), dewormer, heartworm test (if over 6 months), rabies (if atleast 16 weeks) and spay/neuter! Puppies will be altered before adoption. All rescues and shelters practice pediatric spay and neuter. This is essential in our rescue efforts and it is a policy that we will stick by. All dogs over 8 weeks and 2 pounds will be altered before adoption. There are no exceptions to this rule on all healthy and adoptable dogs. 

Puppies/Dogs that are not available for adoption due to vetting not being complete can be reserved with an approved application and a non refundable $50 deposit. This deposit is applied to your adoption fee and the remaining $125 is due at pick up.

Wags and Whiskers is an all-volunteer rescue. We also have full-time jobs and Families. We will try to answer all questions and applications in a timely manner. Please be patient and bear with us . Do not contact Parkway Animal Hospital as they are a vet clinic and can not answer questions on behalf of Wags and Whiskers. All questions and comments must go directly through the rescue. Thank you for your understanding.

ADOPTION APPLICATION

https://form.jotform.us/70898112177159

animal.description:
Little Luna! Luna is an adorable, healthy and sweet puppy, she has had DNA test and is half Siberian Husky (she has a speckle of blue in her right eye) and some German Shepherd also, she is about 6-7 months old and 37 lbs. She is a medium/high energy dog who needs regular exercise. 

Please read all about Luna (below) and if you feel you are a good match for her and want to meet her, please complete an application found on our website, we will be adopting Luna into the Portland area only.
www.mywayhomedogrescue.org

Luna had an under socialized beginning but she has gained so much confidence in a very short time. She is smart and learns very quickly. She is crate trained and does well on leash. She is still working on her house-training skills but does follow the other dogs outside. So, if she is let out often she rarely has an accident. Luna loves other dogs and is very playful with her dog friends. She also LOVES snow!

Luna loves car rides but has gotten sick each time she has been in a car. She has not been tested with cats or tested with small dogs. She is shy with new people but is learning quickly that the people who her foster parents introduces her to are ok. No kids please, she is afraid of their energy. 

Luna’s perfect home will have an active person or couple with another playful dog(s), and a secure yard. She needs people who have the time and energy to work with her to create amazing dog she is becoming. We are not placing Luna with children or cats. Luna is an amazing little puppy who is looking for an amazing person(s) who wants to work with a smart dog! 

Luna has had her vaccinations, heart wormed tested, has been spayed, de-wormed, had flea treatment, and is microchipped. Her adoption fee is $350.
